cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL 

This paper is about using machine learning to predict runtime distributions of algorithms for solving hard combinatorial problems in artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses neural networks for prediction, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves statistical analysis and modeling, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper specifically mentions SAT solving and AI planning, which could suggest cs.PL (Programming Languages and Compilers) as a possible sub-category.
